This week, security researchers started speaking out about security lapses in the program, the new trend of "Zoombombing," and crashing public meetings with obscenities and worse.
Some common-sense tips on safer usage of Zoom.
Be wary of linksZoom meetings start by creating a meeting and copying a URL that is generated by Zoom.
On the general Zoom settings app window, there is an option for screen sharing.
There you instruct Zoom to only let the Host share the screen.